[Tofuunion at Japundit reports](http://japundit.com/2010/12/02/immigrants-or-
temporary-workers-a-visionary-call-for-a-%E2%80%9Cjapanese-style-immigration-
nation%E2%80%9D/) on the latest figures released by the Health, Labor and
Welfare Ministry of Japan according to which “Japan’s population has shrunken
since 2008 and continues to decrease at an accelerating rate”. According to
the post, the government has been implementing a new immigration plan to cope
with the labor shortage, which would have a dramatic impact on the country's
economy.

